title: ABC's Sarah Ferguson sinks to ‘new low’ during Josh Frydenberg interview
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio says ABC host Sarah Ferguson sank to a "new low” in her interview with Josh Frydenberg.  “Hang your head in shame, Sarah Ferguson, what a disgrace.” Ms De Giorgio said.  “How could she possibly ask that question of a Jewish Australian?”

title: Angus Taylor visits 'beautiful vigil' for Bondi Beach massacre victims
description: Shadow Defence Minister Angus Taylor has met with Sharri Markson to discuss the Bondi Beach massacre and how antisemitism is being handled in Australia.

title: ‘Highly offensive’: Councillor wears keffiyeh after the Bondi massacre
description: Sky News Senior Reporter Caroline Marcus says it was “highly offensive” for a Victorian councillor to wear a keffiyeh after the Bondi massacre.  Councillor Sue Bolton has received criticism for wearing a keffiyeh during a Bondi massacre mourning.  Ms Bolton rejected the idea that any symbol of Palestine is ‘anti-Jewish’.

title: Anthony Albanese gives ‘admission of failure’ on failed antisemitism action
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio says Prime Minister Anthony Albanese’s announcement on antisemitism action today is an “admission of failure.”  “This is truly reprehensible on the part of the prime minister and Labor,” Ms De Giorgio said.  “Anthony Albanese has failed in this moment and failed from the start.”

title: ‘Groundbreaking’: Melania documentary ‘most expensive ever made’
description: Sky News host Freya Leach details the documentary about First Lady Melania Trump.  “If you are looking for something to stream … a groundbreaking new documentary is about to be released and it’s all about Melania Trump,” Ms Leach said.  “This is the … most expensive documentary ever made, costing $60 million.”

title: ‘Strength wins’: Trump’s ‘first class performance’ on critical issues
description: Former Victoria Liberal Party president Michael Kroger claims US President Donald Trump’s performance on the Middle East, antisemitism, and borders has been “first class.”  Mr Kroger told Sky News host Rita Panahi, Trump has been “outstanding on disgusting antisemitism at American universities,” Mr Kroger told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “In Australia, we can’t say the same thing.”

title: ‘Unbelievably stupid’: Susie Wiles under scrutiny for sitting down with ‘anti-Trump’ Vanity Fair
description: Centre of the American Experiment President John Hinderaker says it was “unbelievably stupid” for White House Chief of Staff Susie Wiles to sit down with Vanity Fair.   “This was unbelievably stupid,” Mr Hinderaker told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “There's no more vicious, anti-Conservative, anti-Trump outlet than Vanity Fair … did Susie Wiles just fall off a turnip truck?”

title: Donald Trump ‘ratcheting up the pressure’ on Venezuelan President Maduro
description: Centre of the American Experiment President John Hinderaker says US President Donald Trump is trying to “ratchet up the pressure” on Venezuelan President Nicolas Maduro.  “We have an aircraft carrier strike force stationed in the Caribbean now off the Venezuelan coast,” Mr Hinderaker told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “President Trump is trying to ratchet up the pressure on Maduro to try and drive him out of office without armed conflict.”

title: Greta Thunberg labelled one of the ‘least self-aware’ people in the world
description: Centre of the American Experiment President John Hinderaker says activist Greta Thunberg is one of the “least self-aware” people in the world.   “Greta Thunberg must be one of the least self-aware people in the world,” Mr Hinderaker told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “The reason why factories have shut down all across Europe is because green energy laws … have driven up the cost of electricity …. Thunberg herself is one of the causes of the problem.”

title: ‘Authority over immigration’: Donald Trump expands travel ban list
description: Centre of the American Experiment President John Hinderaker says US President Donald Trump has expanded the travel ban list.  “It’s a huge list … the President has got a lot of authority over immigration,” Mr Hinderaker told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “He’s chosen to do that now.”

title: ‘Sorry is the hardest word to say for Anthony Albanese’: James Paterson
description: Shadow Finance Minister James Paterson claims Prime Minister Anthony Albanese’s reluctance to “concede error” on the Bondi attack “diminishes his leadership”.

title: ‘Not accountable’: ABC ‘stands by’ Laura Tingle’s ‘contemptuous’ comments on Bondi attack
description: Sky News Digital Editor Jack Houghton wrote to the ABC over Laura Tingle’s comments that the Bondi attack was not religiously motivated.  “I personally wrote to Hugh Marks and Justin Stevens, who are the two leaders that are responsible for this Laura Tingle mess,” Mr Houghton told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “The ABC communications team wrote back to me, and they stood by it.  “The podcast is still live.”

title: ‘Call it out’: Albanese omits ‘radical Islam’ in his ‘admission of failure’ on antisemitism action
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio claims Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has omitted radical Islam in his “admission of failure” today.  “The common denominator is radical Islam,” Ms De Giorgio said.  “Call it out for what it is, radical Islam.  “It’s a religious ideology that has no place in Australia.”

title: ‘Has to stop’: Australian universities blasted for ‘fostering’ antisemitic activity
description: Shadow Home Affairs Minister Jonathon Duniam claims Australian universities have been “marginalising Jewish university students.”  “They are getting taxpayers' money with no consequences, no penalties whatsoever,” Mr Duniam told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “Allowing this sort of behavior to happen has to stop.”

title: EXCLUSIVE: Netanyahu pleads for Australia to ‘Wake up’
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu pleads with the Australian government to wake up and protect the Jewish community after the Bondi Massacre.  “I called for the intensification of security arrangements around Jewish institution,” Mr Netanyahu said to Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “Stop them before they act.  “I say now to the Australian Government, dammit, wake up, you don’t need any more warnings, you’ve already received enough.”
